<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED0FFF8DFF54F8EDFDCEF815" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="B534515BED0FFF8DFF54F8EDFDCEF815" blockId="29.[151,1437,1775,2018]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0FFF8DFF54F8EDFECCF8DD" bold="true" box="[199,334,1883,1909]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Etymology.</emphasis>
The specific epithet is from “Minotaurus”, a monster with a human body and a bull’s head in Ancient Greek mythology, living in labyrinth, and refers to the strong carapace and the labyrinth-like copulatory ducts of the new species; noun in apposition.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED0FFF8EFF54F871FB0BFF7D" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="181" pageId="29" pageNumber="180" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="B534515BED0FFF8EFF54F871FB0BFF7D" blockId="29.[151,1437,1775,2018]" lastBlockId="30.[151,1437,150,573]" lastPageId="30" lastPageNumber="181" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0FFF8DFF54F871FEC0F849" bold="true" box="[199,322,1991,2017]" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Differs from all congeners by the absence of CPSB on the cephalon (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0FFF8DFBC5F871FB76F84A" box="[1110,1268,1991,2018]" captionStart="FIGURES 145–149" captionStartId="30.[151,264,1730,1754]" captionTargetBox="[150,1438,596,1707]" captionTargetId="figure-214@30.[150,1438,596,1707]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURES 145–149. Living spiders of Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov. (© Wayne P. Maddison). 145, 147. Male; 146, 148–149. Female." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500829/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">Figs 145–146</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0FFF8DFA93F871FAE7F84A" box="[1280,1381,1991,2018]" captionStart="FIGURES 150–157" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 150–157. Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (150, 152, 153, 156) and female (151, 154–155, 157). 150–151. Habitus, in dorsal (150–151) and lateral (152) view; 153, 155. Details of chelicerae, in dorsal (153) and back (155) view, arrows show the triangular projections; 154. Sternum; 156–157. Front view of carapace." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500831/files/figure.png" pageId="29" pageNumber="180">150–151</figureCitation>
), the embolus coiled for more than four circles, the absence of LED (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFCFBFF20FC4FFF19" box="[872,973,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 158–160" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1062,1086]" captionTargetBox="[274,1309,181,1029]" captionTargetId="figure-19@32.[274,1313,181,1038]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 158–160. Palp of Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (158), ventral (159) and retrolateral (160) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500833" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500833/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Figs 159</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFC49FF20FB85FF19" box="[986,1031,150,177]" captionStart="FIGURES 161–163" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox="[289,1297,1150,1938]" captionTargetId="figure-44@32.[282,1304,1146,1944]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 161–163. Palp of Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (161), ventral (162) and retrolateral (163) view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500835" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500835/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">162</figureCitation>
), the relatively wide and thick carapace, and the copulatory ducts swerving for more than 15 times (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFCFDFF0CFBFEFF7D" box="[878,1148,186,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 164–169" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-19@33.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 164–169. Female genitalia of Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 164, 167. Ventral view; 165, 166, 168. Dorsal view; 169. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500837/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Figs 165–166, 168–169</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="FD9102D0ED0CFF8FFF54FF68FCD5FF51" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="182" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" type="description">
<paragraph id="B534515BED0CFF8EFF54FF68FC12FD95" blockId="30.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0CFF8EFF54FF68FE26FF50" bold="true" box="[199,420,222,248]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Description. Male.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFD06FF68FD74FF51" box="[661,758,222,249]" captionStart="FIGURES 150–157" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 150–157. Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (150, 152, 153, 156) and female (151, 154–155, 157). 150–151. Habitus, in dorsal (150–151) and lateral (152) view; 153, 155. Details of chelicerae, in dorsal (153) and back (155) view, arrows show the triangular projections; 154. Sternum; 156–157. Front view of carapace." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500831/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Fig. 150</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 2.73; abdomen length 1.80. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.54, ALE 0.30, PME 0.10, PLE 0.28. Measurements of legs: I 4.95 (1.58, 0.84, 1.19, 0.77, 0.57), II 3.73 (1.26, 0.61, 0.79, 0.65, 0.42), III 3.86 (1.37, 0.58, 0.67, 0.72, 0.52), IV 3.99 (1.28, 0.50, 0.88, 0.83, 0.50). Chelicerae with small triangular projection distally (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFD48FEFCFCBEFECD" box="[731,828,330,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 150–157" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 150–157. Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (150, 152, 153, 156) and female (151, 154–155, 157). 150–151. Habitus, in dorsal (150–151) and lateral (152) view; 153, 155. Details of chelicerae, in dorsal (153) and back (155) view, arrows show the triangular projections; 154. Sternum; 156–157. Front view of carapace." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500831/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Fig. 153</figureCitation>
); promargin with two stout teeth, retromargin with one bicuspid tooth. Palp (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFE17FED8FDA6FE21" box="[388,548,366,393]" captionStart-0="FIGURES 158–160" captionStart-1="FIGURES 161–163" captionStartId-0="32.[151,264,1062,1086]" captionStartId-1="32.[151,264,1968,1992]" captionTargetBox-0="[274,1309,181,1029]" captionTargetBox-1="[289,1297,1150,1938]" captionTargetId-0="figure-19@32.[274,1313,181,1038]" captionTargetId-1="figure-44@32.[282,1304,1146,1944]" captionTargetPageId-0="32" captionTargetPageId-1="32" captionText-0="FIGURES 158–160. Palp of Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (158), ventral (159) and retrolateral (160) view." captionText-1="FIGURES 161–163. Palp of Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., in prolateral (161), ventral (162) and retrolateral (163) view." figureDoi-0="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500833" figureDoi-1="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500835" httpUri-0="https://zenodo.org/record/6500833/files/figure.png" httpUri-1="https://zenodo.org/record/6500835/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Figs 158–163</figureCitation>
): yellowish brown; embolus slender and long, coiled for more than four circles; embolic disc large, slightly sclerotized, without LED; tegulum slightly sclerotized, tegular lobe present; salticid radix slightly sclerotized; both retrolateral and prolateral sperm duct loops present; retrolateral tibial apophysis relatively narrow and long, intermediately curved. Sternum with setal tuft sub-centrally. Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFABDFE6CFA12FE5D" box="[1326,1424,474,501]" captionStart="FIGURES 150–157" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 150–157. Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (150, 152, 153, 156) and female (151, 154–155, 157). 150–151. Habitus, in dorsal (150–151) and lateral (152) view; 153, 155. Details of chelicerae, in dorsal (153) and back (155) view, arrows show the triangular projections; 154. Sternum; 156–157. Front view of carapace." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500831/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Fig. 150</figureCitation>
): carapace reddish brown to dark, without CPSB; dorsal abdomen pale yellowish with brown markings, slightly sclerotized; legs yellowish brown, with annuli and pale yellowish setae.
</paragraph>
<caption id="E1F401D3ED0CFF8EFF04F974FE77F957" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500829" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6500829" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500829/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" startId="30.[151,264,1730,1754]" targetBox="[150,1438,596,1707]" targetPageId="30">
<paragraph id="B534515BED0CFF8EFF04F974FE77F957" blockId="30.[151,1436,1730,1791]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0CFF8EFF04F974FEECF972" bold="true" box="[151,366,1730,1754]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">FIGURES 145–149.</emphasis>
Living spiders of 
<taxonomicName id="728B2AD8ED0CFF8EFDB9F975FB8BF973" authority="Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityName="Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang" authorityYear="2022" box="[554,1033,1731,1755]" class="Arachnida" family="Salticidae" genus="Charippus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="minotaurus" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0CFF8EFDB9F975FC8DF972" box="[554,783,1731,1755]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Charippus minotaurus</emphasis>
Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0CFF8EFB87F975FBE4F973" bold="true" box="[1044,1126,1731,1755]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="9CCC3032ED0CFF8EFB87F975FBE4F973" box="[1044,1126,1731,1755]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(© Wayne P. Maddison). 145, 147. Male; 146, 148–149. Female.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="B534515BED0CFF8FFF54F89BFC74FF7D" blockId="30.[151,1437,1837,2043]" lastBlockId="31.[151,1436,150,286]" lastPageId="31" lastPageNumber="182" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0CFF8EFF54F89BFEA7F8EF" bold="true" box="[199,293,1837,1863]" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Female.</emphasis>
Habitus as shown in 
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFD87F89BFDF6F8E0" box="[532,628,1837,1864]" captionStart="FIGURES 150–157" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 150–157. Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (150, 152, 153, 156) and female (151, 154–155, 157). 150–151. Habitus, in dorsal (150–151) and lateral (152) view; 153, 155. Details of chelicerae, in dorsal (153) and back (155) view, arrows show the triangular projections; 154. Sternum; 156–157. Front view of carapace." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500831/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Fig. 151</figureCitation>
. Carapace length 2.78; abdomen length 2.66. Chelicerae (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFB69F89BFADBF8E0" box="[1274,1369,1837,1864]" captionStart="FIGURES 150–157" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 150–157. Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (150, 152, 153, 156) and female (151, 154–155, 157). 150–151. Habitus, in dorsal (150–151) and lateral (152) view; 153, 155. Details of chelicerae, in dorsal (153) and back (155) view, arrows show the triangular projections; 154. Sternum; 156–157. Front view of carapace." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500831/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Fig. 155</figureCitation>
) as in male but without small apophysis. Measurements of eyes: AME 0.60, ALE 0.30, PME 0.08, PLE 0.24. Measurements of legs: I 4.28 (1.38, 0.74, 0.99, 0.64, 0.53), II 3.56 (1.27, 0.57, 0.72, 0.55, 0.45), III 3.67 (1.33, 0.65, 0.59, 0.63, 0.47), IV 4.23 (1.36, 0.64, 0.84, 0.78, 0.61). Color in alcohol (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFC0AF82FFC7FF81C" box="[921,1021,1945,1972]" captionStart="FIGURES 150–157" captionStartId="31.[151,264,1782,1806]" captionTargetBox="[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetId="figure-59@31.[156,1430,309,1759]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 150–157. Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov., male (150, 152, 153, 156) and female (151, 154–155, 157). 150–151. Habitus, in dorsal (150–151) and lateral (152) view; 153, 155. Details of chelicerae, in dorsal (153) and back (155) view, arrows show the triangular projections; 154. Sternum; 156–157. Front view of carapace." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500831" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500831/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Fig. 151</figureCitation>
): carapace as in male; abdomen pale yellow with brown markings. Setal tuft on sternum as in male. Epigynum (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0CFF8EFC45F80BFBF6F870" box="[982,1140,1981,2008]" captionStart="FIGURES 164–169" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-19@33.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 164–169. Female genitalia of Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 164, 167. Ventral view; 165, 166, 168. Dorsal view; 169. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500837/files/figure.png" pageId="30" pageNumber="181">Figs 164, 167</figureCitation>
): window relatively small, rims not obviously sclerotized, median septum wide, extending to area near genital furrow; lateral depressions deep. Vulva (
<figureCitation id="2DB04DDEED0DFF8FFF79FF21FE46FF1A" box="[234,452,150,178]" captionStart="FIGURES 164–169" captionStartId="33.[151,264,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,181,1516]" captionTargetId="figure-19@33.[151,1436,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="33" captionText="FIGURES 164–169. Female genitalia of Charippus minotaurus Yu, Maddison &amp; Zhang, sp. nov.. 164, 167. Ventral view; 165, 166, 168. Dorsal view; 169. CD path." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6500837" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6500837/files/figure.png" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">Figs 165–166, 168</figureCitation>
): CD extremely long and coiled, swerving for more than 15 times, slightly widened at origin; AG small and oval; spermathecae prominent, bulging, kidney shaped.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B534515BED0DFF8FFF54FF69FCD5FF51" blockId="31.[151,1436,150,286]" box="[199,855,222,249]" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">
<emphasis id="87FF8D49ED0DFF8FFF54FF69FE07FF50" bold="true" box="[199,389,222,249]" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">Natural history.</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="6A30EFF9ED0DFF8FFE2CFF69FDA3FF51" box="[447,545,223,249]" pageId="31" pageNumber="182">holotype</typeStatus>
was collected in dry sticks.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
